President Donald J. Trump will host Prime Minister Shinzo Abe of Japan at Mar-a-Lago from April 17-18, 2018. The purpose of their third summit meeting is to reaffirm the alliance between the United States and Japan as a foundation for peace, stability, and prosperity in the Indo-Pacific region. The two leaders will discuss strategies to maintain maximum pressure on North Korea leading up to President Trump's upcoming meeting with North Korean leader Kim Jong Un. Additionally, they will explore ways to expand fair and reciprocal trade and investment ties between the two countries, both of which have strong economies.